caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 3.
Sexual characters of 

Sandalodesmus joachimadisi


n. sp.
A.

Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, mesal view. 
B.
Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, lateral view. 
C.
Holotype ♂ (FCE-Myr 0664), left gonopod, ventral view. 
D.
Paratype ♀ (FCE-Myr 0664), left vulva, ventral view. 
Abbreviations: Ap:
acropodital process; 
Ca:
cannula; 
Cx:
coxa; 
Ev:
external valve; 
Iv:
internal valve; 
Op:
operculum; 
Pf:
prefemur; 
PfP:
prefemoral process; 
Pg:
prostatic groove; 
S:
solenomere; 
SpP:
spiniform process. 
Scale bars:
0.5 mm (
A–C
), 0.2 mm (
D
). Photographed by: Damián Hagopián.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Female
(
paratype
, FCE-Myr 0664). Coloration and body features as in male except that the coxae on body ring 3 with a small process. Posterior margin of vulvae aperture smooth, without projections. Vulvae (
Fig. 3D
) oval shaped in ventral view and elliptical shaped in lateral view. External and internal valves unequal in size, external valve (
Ev
) longer than internal valve (
Iv
), in ventral/distal view. Internal edges of both valves irregular in the medial portion. Both valves with scattered setae in comparison with operculum (
Op
). Operculum about 1/3 of the size of valves, typical for chelodesmids. Total length: 38.04. Width total: 4.95. Telson 1.3 long. Posterior margin of the vulvae aperture: 1.57 wide. Vulvae: 0.79 long, 0.55 wide. External valve: 0.72 long, 0.21 wide. Internal valve: 0.68 long, 0.31 wide. Operculum: 0.12 long, 0.31 wide.
